Data: It's been 3 months since I joinedEventIronfull-time. Some of you must be wondering how is it going and why I was not active on LinkedIn or in any other community.¬†I felt I owe you an update.When I joinEventIronin April, my goal for the next 3 months was to streamline the internal processes, and documentation, hire the right people to work with us, work with our customers closely to make sure they are happy with our services, and create a sustainable business to help grow this company and people.After 3 months, I can proudly say that with the help of great support from our customers and employees, we are able to achieve what we planned for. Today, we are working with 8 customers (some are fortune 500, enterprises, and startups.) around the globe, we are a team of close to 30 people and we have a good process set up internally¬†to guide us.We are supporting our customers on multiple fronts today:1. Email Marketing and Marketing Automation. We support customers onAdobe Marketo,HubSpot,SFMC, andEloquatoday.2. Managing the complete MarTech stack3. Managing the data governance4. Custom integration using custom API development5. Custom Integration usingWorkato,Zapier,Tray.io, etc6. Data cleanup and data discovery using D&B (Dun & Bradstreet),ZoomInfo,LeadIQ,LinkedInSales Navigator, etc7. Custom email and landing page development8. Custom JavaScript development9. Data Analysis and custom report development usingTableau,Microsoft Power BI, Google Data Studio, etcWith the support of our team, customers, and great support from the community, I'm sure we will grow and reach more heights in the coming months.Stay tuned, we have something exciting planned to be launched by end of this year. Will keep you posted. :)#startups#business#team#work#peopleThe Marketing Automation Blog

The term ‚Äòcloud-native‚Äô really means that a specific approach was used while building the application.Specifically, cloud native applications are built around several small, self-contained services (referred to as ‚ÄòMicroservices‚Äô) that are deployed on cloud infrastructure using containers. In summary, ‚Äòcloud-native‚Äô applications have the following characteristics:üìå Can be deployed to any type of cloud.üìå Take full advantage of cloud computing environments and scale up on demand, very fast.üìå Generally are composed of several ‚ÄòMicroservices‚Äô, each providing a single business feature and communicating with each other via a well-defined set of APIs. These services, when combined, provide the application, its functionality.üìå Have an underlying infrastructure that supports continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD), which helps developers constantly add new features/functionality.üìå Make use of containers (such as Docker) to host the above services. Each container maintains resource isolation. It is these containers that provide a fast and easy way to provide additional services on demand.üìå Some way of managing the containers that host these services, the most popular being Kubernetes.FollowCloudnloud Tech Community#cloudnloud#AWS#linux#azure#ansible#docker#kubernetes#automation#jobs#fresher#jobseekers#tech#community#technology#career#cka#ckad#exam#software#microservices
